GOAL

Create an Etsy listing that helps a buyer quickly understand:

- exactly what is being sold;
- whether it is physical or digital;
- who made, designed, sourced, or selected it;
- what the buyer receives;
- how the product is used;
- which options and personalization choices are available;
- what materials, dimensions, formats, and compatibility conditions apply;
- how processing, delivery, or digital access works;
- which limitations or requirements matter;
- what makes the item meaningfully different.

The listing should support Etsy search while remaining natural, accurate, easy to scan, and useful to a real buyer.

Prioritize clarity, trust, product accuracy, and purchase confidence over keyword density or exaggerated sales language.

ACCURACY AND COMPLIANCE

1. Use only facts, specifications, materials, dimensions, formats, features, policies, prices, timelines, and benefits supplied in the prompt.

2. Do not invent:

- materials;
- dimensions;
- file formats;
- file sizes;
- colors;
- variations;
- compatibility;
- included accessories;
- production methods;
- shipping times;
- processing times;
- certifications;
- sustainability claims;
- warranties;
- refund terms;
- commercial-use rights;
- personalization options;
- customer results;
- awards;
- ratings;
- sales numbers;
- scarcity;
- discounts;
- guarantees.

3. Do not describe the product as handmade, hand-drawn, hand-sewn, hand-painted, vintage, organic, sustainable, recycled, non-toxic, hypoallergenic, licensed, certified, professional-grade, or ethically sourced unless that claim was explicitly confirmed.

4. Do not label a product as vintage unless its eligibility was confirmed.

5. Do not imply that a mass-produced item was personally handmade by the seller.

6. Clearly and accurately represent the seller’s role:

- made by the seller;
- designed by the seller;
- sourced by the seller;
- handpicked by the seller;
- produced by a disclosed production partner.

7. If a production partner is used, do not describe the physical manufacturing as performed entirely by the seller.

8. If AI-assisted creation was involved, do not claim that the work was completely hand-drawn or manually illustrated unless accurate.

9. Do not invent or conceal commercial printing, print-on-demand production, manufacturing, or fulfillment arrangements.

10. Do not use competitor names, celebrity names, fictional franchises, song lyrics, movie titles, sports teams, designer brands, unauthorized characters, or other protected intellectual property unless the rights were explicitly confirmed.

11. Do not imply endorsement by Etsy.

12. Do not claim guaranteed medical, financial, emotional, educational, safety, or performance outcomes.

13. If necessary information is missing, use an explicit placeholder such as:

[Information required: exact material]

Do not fill missing information with assumptions.

TITLE

Write one recommended Etsy listing title.

Title requirements:

- maximum 140 characters, including spaces;
- preferably fewer than 15 words when the product can be described clearly within that length;
- state what the item actually is;
- place the most important identifying information early;
- include only the strongest objective product traits;
- remain easy to understand on mobile;
- use the primary search phrase naturally;
- avoid unnecessary repetition;
- avoid turning the title into a list of keyword fragments.

A useful title structure may be:

[Item type] + [most important objective trait] + [material, size, style, or use case]

Include recipient, occasion, or holiday terminology only when it is essential to the nature of the item.

Do not automatically add phrases such as:

- gift for her;
- gift for him;
- birthday gift;
- Christmas gift;
- perfect gift;
- unique gift;

unless they genuinely help identify the product and are supported by the item.

Do not include:

- price;
- discount;
- free shipping;
- sale language;
- shop name unless necessary;
- subjective praise;
- excessive punctuation;
- ALL CAPS;
- keyword repetition;
- competitor brands;
- unsupported claims.

Avoid title language such as:

- beautiful;
- amazing;
- perfect;
- best;
- must-have;
- premium;
- luxury;
- unique;

unless the term is objectively meaningful and supported.

Provide:

- recommended title;
- character count;
- word count;
- primary phrase used.

DESCRIPTION

Write one complete Etsy listing description.

The first two sentences should:

- clearly identify the product;
- naturally include the most relevant search phrase;
- explain the main use or value;
- avoid copying the title word for word;
- help the buyer understand what is being sold without expanding the full description.

Use a scannable structure selected from the following sections.

Include only sections relevant to the product.

Recommended description structure:

1. Opening overview
2. Product highlights
3. What the buyer receives
4. Materials or file details
5. Dimensions and sizing
6. Variations
7. Personalization
8. How to order
9. Processing or delivery
10. Digital download instructions
11. How to use
12. Care instructions
13. Compatibility or software requirements
14. License and permitted use
15. Important limitations
16. Returns, exchanges, or cancellation note
17. Brief closing statement

DESCRIPTION RULES

- Use short paragraphs and meaningful section headings.
- Use bullets where they improve readability.
- Explain concrete product details before emotional or decorative language.
- Connect confirmed features to practical benefits.
- Keep the buyer’s likely questions in mind.
- Explain what is not included when a photo or mockup could create confusion.
- State whether props, frames, furniture, devices, or accessories shown in images are excluded.
- Mention natural variation when handmade materials may differ, but only when relevant.
- Explain color-display or printing variation only when relevant.
- Keep policy language concise and consistent with actual shop policies.
- Do not duplicate the entire listing title.
- Do not repeat the same keyword in every paragraph.
- Do not make the description a keyword list.
- Do not include irrelevant shop history.
- Do not invent testimonials.
- Do not use fake urgency.
- Do not pressure the buyer.

PHYSICAL PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

For physical products, clearly explain:

- materials;
- dimensions;
- weight when relevant;
- available sizes or colors;
- package quantity;
- handmade or production method;
- personalization;
- processing time;
- what is included;
- care instructions;
- compatibility or intended use;
- important safety or age restrictions;
- shipping or delivery context.

Do not describe an item as ready to ship when it is made to order.

Do not invent delivery dates.

DIGITAL PRODUCT DESCRIPTION

For digital products, clearly state near the beginning:

- this is a digital product;
- no physical item will be shipped;
- whether it is an instant download or made-to-order file;
- which files the buyer receives;
- file formats;
- dimensions or resolution;
- software or account requirements;
- editing limitations;
- license terms;
- printing or use instructions;
- how the buyer accesses the files.

For instant digital downloads:

- do not promise email delivery unless that is the actual process;
- explain that access follows Etsy’s digital-download process;
- ensure file count and file size are based on supplied information;
- do not generate variation options when the digital listing does not support them.

For made-to-order digital products:

- explain what the buyer must submit;
- state the confirmed production timeline;
- explain proof and revision handling;
- distinguish the preview from the final file.

Do not imply that:

- Canva Pro is included;
- paid fonts are included;
- a commercial license is included;
- files can be edited in every program;
- all printers will produce identical colors;

unless confirmed.

PERSONALIZATION INSTRUCTIONS

When personalization is available, write one concise buyer-facing personalization instruction.

It should clearly state:

- what information the buyer must enter;
- acceptable spelling and capitalization;
- available options;
- character limits;
- whether personalization is required;
- whether a proof will be sent;
- how revisions work;
- what happens when incomplete information is submitted.

Do not ask buyers to provide unnecessary sensitive information.

Do not promise unlimited revisions unless confirmed.

Also provide:

Personalization field label:
[Short label]

Personalization instructions:
[Clear buyer instruction]

Example response:
[Accurate example]

VARIATIONS

Suggest buyer-facing variation labels only from confirmed options.

For each variation provide:

- variation name;
- option labels;
- any price or availability note only when supplied;
- whether a matching photo is available.

Do not create options that do not exist.

Do not combine unrelated options in a confusing way.

Do not promise custom colors, sizes, or formats unless available.

TAGS

Generate exactly 13 Etsy tags.

Each tag must:

- contain no more than 20 characters, including spaces;
- be relevant to the actual product;
- use natural buyer search language;
- preferably use a multi-word phrase;
- cover distinct search intent;
- avoid repeating the same combination of words;
- remain accurate to the listing.

Use a balanced mix of:

- exact item type;
- style;
- material;
- use case;
- recipient;
- occasion;
- size or format;
- personalization;
- problem or need;
- niche buyer intent.

Do not waste tags by repeating:

- exact category wording;
- exact attribute wording;
- identical singular and plural forms;
- the same phrase in a different order;
- the same main keyword 13 times.

Do not include:

- competitor names;
- unauthorized trademarks;
- irrelevant popular searches;
- misleading recipient or occasion terms;
- hashtags;
- punctuation used only to manipulate search;
- “free shipping”;
- “sale”;
- “best”;
- “cheap”;
- “trending” unless factually relevant.

For each tag provide its character count.

CATEGORY AND SUBCATEGORY

Suggest:

- one primary Etsy category;
- one most specific likely subcategory;
- one alternative category only when genuinely relevant.

Do not claim that the suggested category definitely exists in the current Etsy interface when it was not supplied.

Label category suggestions:

Verify against the current Etsy category selector before publishing.

Do not choose a broad category when a more specific one is clearly supported.

ATTRIBUTES

Create an attribute checklist using only confirmed information.

Possible attributes include:

- primary color;
- secondary color;
- material;
- size;
- style;
- pattern;
- room;
- occasion;
- holiday;
- recipient;
- shape;
- orientation;
- craft type;
- digital file type.

Do not invent attribute values.

Do not repeat exact attribute phrases as standalone tags when another tag could add new search coverage.

MATERIALS

Create a ready-to-enter materials list only when materials were supplied.

Use concise material names.

Do not add:

- packaging materials;
- tools;
- manufacturing equipment;
- shipping supplies;

unless they are genuinely part of the sold item.

Do not claim precious metals, natural gemstones, organic fabric, archival paper, food-safe materials, or hypoallergenic components unless confirmed.

SEARCH PHRASE COVERAGE

After writing the title, description, tags, category, and attributes, verify that the listing covers the important buyer intents without keyword stuffing.

Check whether the package naturally communicates:

- what the item is;
- what it is made from;
- who it is for;
- how it is used;
- its style;
- its format or size;
- whether it is personalized;
- whether it is physical or digital.

Do not force every keyword into every field.

PHOTO AND VIDEO PLAN

Create a practical listing visual plan using only supplied or realistically creatable assets.

Provide 5–10 image ideas when appropriate.

For every image provide:

- purpose;
- what should be visible;
- recommended composition;
- short optional text overlay;
- buyer question answered;
- alt text.

