TEMPLATE BODY

The template body should:

- establish context;
- use variables naturally;
- remain meaningful with sample values;
- avoid excessive variables;
- avoid vague placeholders;
- avoid unsupported urgency;
- include essential conditions;
- match the selected category.

Do not write:

“Hello {{1}}, your {{2}} is ready. Click {{3}}.”

without defining every variable and verifying the structure.

TEMPLATE SAMPLE VALUES

Provide a safe sample for every variable.

Sample values should:

- resemble the expected format;
- contain no real customer data;
- contain no production credentials;
- avoid real payment information;
- show realistic maximum length when possible.

Do not use:

- real phone numbers;
- real order numbers;
- real customer names;
- active promo codes;
- production URLs

unless explicitly approved.

